<HEAD>Quotes From The Candidates, Others</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some quotes from political figures
Sunday:
   
   DAN QUAYLE, the Republican vice presidential nominee, in an
interview with The Associated Press: ``I will eventually be an
asset to the ticket. I feel that I have a lot to offer in
leadership. I feel I have a lot to offer in the area of national
defense. I feel that I have worked very hard in the area of arms
control.''
   
   LLOYD BENTSEN, the Democratic vice presidential nominee, on
Quayle's qualifications: ``Now, I wouldn't say that he couldn't
grow into the job; he probably could. But if a tragedy befell a
president, you'd have to be able to move in immediately and take
over and do what has to be done in facing whatever issues that
confront you at that time.''
   
   GEORGE BUSH, the Republican presidential nominee, on his showing
in the polls: ``I think it's very encouraging movement in the
polls, but these things change so dramatically. ... I can't deny
it's encouraging, but there's certainly nothing there that makes me
relax.''
   
   JESSE JACKSON, on efforts by Democrats to recapture those who
voted for Reagan: ``Well, I would think that the Democrats'
strength is not between the 45-yard lines. ... It will be the
unregistered voters who need to be inspired.''
